ly%2C%20and%20is%20raising%20concerns%20among%20techies%20and%20smartphone%20users%20after%20it%20was%20first%20discussed%20on%20a%20podcast%20named%20'The%20TJ%20Show'.%20The%20term%20is%20used%20to%20describe%20a%20visible%20mark%20or%20indentation%20on%20the%20little%20finger%2C%20likely%20caused%20by%20extensive%20usage%20of%20smartphones%20such%20as%20Apple%20iPhones.%20Tech%20enthusiasts%20are%20convinced%20that%20the%20pinky%20they%20use%20to%20support%20their%20phones%20has%20a%20noticeable%20divet%2C%20appearing%20to%20differ%20from%20the%20appendage%20on%20the%20opposite%20hand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20we%20hold%20our%20phones%20sometimes%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20phone%20resting%20on%20your%20pinky%20finger%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20hosts%20explained%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC4x3xZMu3kN%2F%5C%22%3Eshow%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20creates%20an%20indentation%20that%20actually%20changes%20the%20way%20your%20pinky%20looks%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20determine%20if%20someone%20has%20an%20%26quot%3BiPhone%20finger%26quot%3B%20-%20also%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bsmartphone%20pinky%26quot%3B%20-%20a%20person%20would%20need%20to%20hold%20out%20both%20little%20fingers%20and%20see%20if%20one%20looks%20noticeably%20different%20from%20the%20other%2C%20specifically%20with%20a%20large%20indent%20on%20their%20dominant%20hand%20that%20would%20likely%20be%20from%20holding%20their%20phones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20%26quot%3BiPhone%20finger%26quot%3B%20a%20health%20concern%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20tech%20enthusiasts%20expressed%20worries%20about%20the%20pinky%20indentation%2C%20health%20experts%20have%20dismissed%20it%20as%20a%20genuine%20medical%20condition.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2024%2F03%2F25%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-iphone-finger-and-how-dangerous-is-it%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dr%20Peter%20Evans%2C%20an%20orthopaedic%20surgeon%20with%20Cleveland%20Clinic%2C%20said%20that%20indents%20or%20gaps%20on%20little%20fingers%20don't%20highlight%20a%20problem.%20%26quot%3BThey%20show%20typical%20pinky%20anatomy%2C%20which%20can%20vary%20widely%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOccupational%20therapist%20%C2%A0April%20Hibbeler%20and%20hand%20surgeon%20Dr.%20Michael%20Geary%20of%20Ortho%20Carolina%20also%20agreed%20with%20Dr%20Evans.%20In%20an%20explanation%20about%20the%20%26quot%3Bmusculoskeletal%20'phenomenon%2C'%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20that%20there%20is%20no%20official%20diagnosis%20for%20%26quot%3BiPhone%20finger%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20possible%20that%20people%20who%20think%20they%20have%20smartphone%20pinky%20could%20have%20an%20underlying%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Dr%20Evans.%20%26quot%3BConstant%20cellphone%20use%20can%20cause%20a%20range%20of%20joint%20problems.%20While%20some%20claims%20of%20injury%20might%20be%20overstated%2C%20others%20are%20real%20and%20involve%20serious%2C%20long-term%20damage%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Evans%20warned%20that%20some%20of%20these%20medical%20problems%20include%20clinodactyly%2C%20a%20genetic%20finger%20malformation%20causing%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20pinky%20to%20bend%20close%20to%20the%20ring%20finger.%20There%20is%20also%20Dupuytren's%20contracture%2C%20which%20happens%20when%20thick%20cords%20form%20beneath%20the%20skin%20over%20years%20and%20yank%20fingers%20close%20to%20the%20palm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Dr%20Evans%20emphasised%20that%20there%20is%20no%20indication%20smartphone%20use%20contributes%20to%20the%20latter.%20But%20he%20warned%20of%20a%20few%20phone-related%20medical%20conditions%20that%20can%20arise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPhone-related%20medical%20conditions%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Dr%20Evans%20debunked%20the%20iPhone%20finger%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3Bsmartphone%20elbow%26quot%3B%20-%20medically%20known%20as%20cubital%20tunnel%20syndrome%20-%20is%20quite%20real.%20He%20explained%20that%20this%20happens%20to%20people%20who%20bend%20their%20elbow%20beyond%2090%20degrees%20in%20long%20durations%2C%20commonly%20to%20text.%20%26quot%3BTingling%20or%20numbness%20in%20your%20pinky%20could%20also%20signal%26quot%3B%20the%20condition%20known%20to%20cause%20nerve%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20doctor%20urged%20smartphone%20users%20to%20be%20on%20guard%20for%20the%20dreaded%20%26quot%3Btexting%20thumb%26quot%3B%20or%20neck.%20%26quot%3BYour%20thumb%20joints%20aren't%20made%20to%20text%20and%20swipe%20all%20day%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOveruse%20can%20aggravate%20underlying%20conditions%2C%20like%20arthritis%2C%20or%20cause%20new%20problems%20in%20the%20thumb%20tendons%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20one's%20neck%2C%20Dr%20Evans%20noted%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bhead%20weighs%20around%2010%20to%2012%20pounds%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20should%20be%20of%20concern%20when%20downward%20gazing%20at%20a%20smartphone.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20look%20down%2C%20you%20increase%20the%20load%20on%20your%20neck%20muscles.%20This%20added%20pressure%20can%20cause%20muscle%20pain%20and%20spasms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715333400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fn82j1e2g_iphone-_625x300_10_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fwhat-is-iphone-finger-and-is-it-dangerous-heres-everything-to-know-5631982%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20term%20%26quot%3BiPhone%20finger%26quot%3B%20has%20gained%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20lately%2C%20and%20is%20raising%20concerns%20among%20techies%20and%20smartphone%20users%20after%20it%20was%20first%20discussed%20on%20a%20podcast%20named%20'The%20TJ%20Show'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0