s%20that%20alter%20its%20operations%20so%20dramatically%20that%20it%20loses%20its%20ubiquity%20in%20the%20search%20and%20advertising%20industries%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20new%20companies%20and%20technologies%20to%20flourish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20antitrust%20cases%20will%20also%20likely%20influence%20the%20outcomes%20of%20other%20antitrust%20lawsuits%20the%20US%20government%20has%20filed%20against%20major%20tech%20companies.%20Currently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Apple%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-business-suite%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20face%20similar%20antitrust%20lawsuits%20against%20their%20business%20practices%20that%20could%20threaten%20their%20market%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e1c9831-9b4b-4c83-8898-757900d949af%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20to%20know%20about%20Google's%20class-action%20settlements%20and%20who%20can%20claim%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20two%20major%20class-action%20lawsuits%20that%20were%20resolved%20or%20nearing%20resolution%20in%20late%202023%20and%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20hotly%20anticipated%20resolutions%20was%20that%20of%20a%20class-action%20case%20involving%20personal%20data%20collected%20from%20136%20million%20Google%20Chrome%20users.%20The%20lawsuit%20accused%20Google%20of%20tracking%20the%20internet%20activity%20of%20users%20who%20had%20switched%20to%20Google's%20%26quot%3Bincognito%26quot%3B%20setting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20a%20settlement%20agreement%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-delete-browsing-data-settle-privacy-lawsuit-incognito-mode-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20said%20it%20would%20delete%20the%20search%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20collected%20from%20those%20136%20million