%20propulsion%20system%20and%20electromagnetic%20catapults.%20Electromagnetic%20catapults%2C%20which%20replace%20conventional%20steam-powered%20catapults%2C%20are%20meant%20to%20reliably%20and%20accurately%20launch%20aircraft%20off%20the%20deck%20of%20the%20Fujian.%20The%20US%20Navy%2C%20still%20considered%20the%20world's%20most%20technologically%20advanced%20Navy%2C%20is%20the%20only%20other%20force%20that%20has%20deployed%20this%20technology%20on%20its%20carriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Fujian%20aircraft%20carrier%20features%20a%20new%20integrated%20propulsion%20system%20and%20electromagnetic%20catapults.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Fujian%20aircraft%20carrier%20features%20a%20new%20integrated%20propulsion%20system%20and%20electromagnetic%20catapults.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F2gr30m5o_fujian-_625x300_10_May_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Fujian%20aircraft%20carrier%20features%20a%20new%20integrated%20propulsion%20system%20and%20electromagnetic%20catapults.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Fujian%20is%20now%20expected%20to%20begin%20trials%20of%20its%20carrier-borne%20aircraft%20soon%20which%20could%20last%20up%20to%20a%20year%20before%20the%20warship%20is%20declared%20operational%20in%20all%20respects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20path%20to%20developing%20aircraft%20carriers%20is%20part%20of%20a%20sustained%20effort%20to%20enhance%20its%20naval%20capabilities%20and%20to%20project%20power%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20first%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20Liaoning%2C%20originally%20a%20Soviet-era%20vessel%2C%20was%20purchased%20from%20Ukraine%20in%201998.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20carrier%20was%20incomplete%20and%20was%20lying%20unused.%20It%20was%20subsequently%20refitted%20and%20commissioned%20into%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy%20(PLAN)%20in%202012.%20Liaoning%20has%20primarily%20been%20used%20for%20training%20purposes%20and%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20China's%20growing%20military%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Chinas%20first%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20was%20acquired%20from%20Ukraine%20in%201998.%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Chinas%20first%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20was%20acquired%20from%20Ukraine%20in%201998.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fqquep77g_liaoning_625x300_10_May_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20first%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20was%20acquired%20from%20Ukraine%20in%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Shandong%2C%20China's%20second%20carrier%20and%20the%20first%20one%20to%20be%20manufactured%20at%20home%2C%20was%20launched%20in%20April%202017%20and%20entered%20service%20in%20December%202019.%20The%20ship%2C%20a%20significantly%20modernised%20variant%20of%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20has%20seen%20operational%20deployments%20involving%20the%20use%20of%20the%20Shenyang%20J-15%20'Flying%20Shark'%20fighter%2C%20a%20variant%20of%20the%20Russian-designed%20Sukhoi%2033%20fighter%20jet%20that%20incorporates%20significant%20Chinese%20modifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20Chinese%20Navy%20is%20developing%20the%20J-35%2C%20a%20carrier-borne%20stealth%20fighter%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20operational%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20J-35%20is%20designed%20to%20operate%20from%20China's%20latest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20the%20Fujian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Navy%20currently%20operates%20two%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20and%20INS%20Vikrant.%20The%20Indian%20Navy%20has%20wanted%20a%20larger%2C%20more%20capable%20aircraft%20carrier%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20only%20to%20be%20rebuffed%20by%20successive%20governments%20concerned%20about%20the%20exorbitant%20cost%20of%20development%2C%20manufacture%20and%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20a%20carrier%20in%20the%20class%20of%20the%20Fujian%20would%20cost%20India%20%247%20billion%20(Rs%2056%2C000%20crore)%20to%20build.%20The%20cost%20of%20new-build%20fighters%20on%20board%20could%20total%20a%20further%20%248%20billion%20(Rs%2065%2C920%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22India%20operates%20two%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20the%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20(in%20the%20distance)%20and%20INS%20Vikrant%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22India%20operates%20two%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20the%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20(in%20the%20distance)%20and%20INS%20Vikrant%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fbs07771g_ins-vikramaditya-ins-vikrat_625x300_10_May_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20operates%20two%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20the%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20(in%20the%20distance)%20and%20INS%20Vikrant%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20government%20is%20considering%20green-lighting%20a%20smaller%20carrier%2C%20of%20the%20same-size%20as%20the%20INS%20Vikrant.%20The%20government%20is%20also%20in%20negotiation%20with%20Dassault%20of%20France%20to%20acquire%2026%20Rafale-M%20fighters%20for%20the%20Vikrant%20at%20an%20approximate%20cost%20of%20%248%20billion%20(Rs%2065%2C920%20crore).%20The%20Rafale-M%20would%20replace%20older%20and%20less%20reliable%20Russian-built%20MiG-29K%20jets%20deployed%20on%20board%20the%20Vikrant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20May%202024%2C%20nine%20countries%20operate%20frontline%20aircraft%20carriers.%20These%20countries%20are%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%2C%20Italy%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20India%2C%20Japan%2C%20France%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20Russia.%20The%20United%20States%20leads%20the%20way%20with%2011%20operational%20carriers%2C%20significantly%20more%20than%20any%20other%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715324220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fhac7a7ro_fujian-_625x300_10_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.n